10 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
11 SECTION 1. That Chapter 12, Title 33, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
12 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
13 ignated as Section 33-1203A, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
14 33-1203A. REGISTERED TEACHER APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM. (1) For pur-
15 poses of this section:
16 (a) "Mentor teacher" means a licensed teacher in good standing with at
17 least three (3) years of licensed educator experience who supervises
18 and guides a teacher apprentice during the apprenticeship period. The
19 mentor teacher supports the training, mentoring, and progress of the
20 teacher apprentice.
21 (b) "Teacher apprentice" means an individual who is registered and
22 enrolled in the registered teacher apprenticeship program and works un-
23 der the supervision of the mentor teacher, learning through on-the-job
24 teaching experience and academic coursework. A teacher apprentice
25 shall not be the teacher of record in any public school while completing
26 the registered teacher apprenticeship program.
27 (2) The state board of education shall establish a registered teacher
28 apprenticeship program, subject to approval by the United States department
29 of labor, which shall provide an alternative structured educational pathway
30 for prospective teachers to obtain a bachelor's degree from an accredited
31 institution and licensure as a teacher through a combination of on-the-job
32 training and academic coursework.
33 (3) In consultation with the state department of education and other
34 relevant stakeholders, the state board of education shall establish eligi-
35 bility requirements and program guidelines in conformity with federal ap-
36 prenticeship standards under 29 CFR 29.5. Such guidelines shall include but
37 are not limited to:
38 (a) The teacher apprentice shall gain classroom experience through di-
39 rect teaching practice under the supervision of the mentor teacher.
40 (b) The mentor teacher shall assist the teacher apprentice with plan-
41 ning and teaching with a continuing gradual increase in teacher appren-
42 tice responsibility.

2
1 (c) The mentor teacher shall assist the teacher apprentice in becoming
2 an effective and competent teacher but shall not serve as an evaluator
3 of the teacher apprentice.
4 (d) A mentor teacher may receive compensation for the mentor teacher
5 services in addition to the educator's salary.
6 (4) Upon completion of the registered teacher apprenticeship program
7 pursuant to this section, a teacher apprentice shall receive a standard cer-
8 tificate and shall be eligible to receive a bachelor's degree from an accred-
9 ited institution and to obtain licensure as a teacher in the state of Idaho.
10 (5) The state board of education may promulgate rules, subject to leg-
11 islative approval, implementing the provisions of this section.
12 SECTION 2. That Section 33-1201, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
13 amended to read as follows:
14 33-1201. CERTIFICATE REQUIRED. (1) Every person who is employed to
15 serve in any elementary or secondary school in the capacity of teacher,
16 supervisor, administrator, education specialist, school nurse, or school
17 librarian shall be required to have and to hold a certificate issued under
18 authority of the state board of education, valid for the service being ren-
19 dered; except that the state board of education may authorize endorsement
20 for use in Idaho, for not more than five (5) years, certificates valid in
21 other states when the qualifications therefor are not lower than those re-
22 quired for an Idaho certificate.
23 (2) No certificate shall be required of a student who is attending any
24 teacher-training institution and serving as a practice teacher or teacher
25 apprentice in a state board of education-approved registered apprenticeship
26 program for teachers in a classroom under the supervision of a certificated
27 teacher and who is jointly assigned by such teacher-training institution and
28 the governing board of a district or a public institution to perform practice
29 teaching or of a student who is participating in the registered teacher ap-
30 prenticeship program pursuant to section 33-1203A, Idaho Code.
31 (3) A student, while serving in a practicum, internship, apprentice-
32 ship, or student teaching position under the supervision of a person cer-
33 tificated pursuant to this section, shall be accorded the same liability in-
34 surance coverage by the school district being served as that accorded such
35 certificated person in the same district, and such student shall comply with
36 all rules and regulations of the school district or public institution while
37 serving in such a capacity.
38 SECTION 3. That Section 33-1203, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
39 amended to read as follows:
40 33-1203. ACCREDITED TEACHER TRAINING REQUIREMENTS. Except in the
41 limited fields of trades and industries and specialists certificates of
42 school librarians and school nurses, the state board shall not authorize the
43 issuance of any standard certificate premised upon less than four (4) years
44 of accredited college training to any person who does not hold a bachelor's
45 degree from an accredited four (4) year institution, including such profes-
46 sional training as the state board may require, or the successful completion
47 of a state board of education-approved registered apprenticeship program

